com.github.jonathanxd.iutils.container

Interface BaseContainer<T>

  • All Superinterfaces:
    java.lang.Comparable<BaseContainer<T>>, UnknownContainer<T>
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    HistoryContainer<T>, IMutableContainer<T>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    Container, ImmutableContainer, MutableContainer, StaticContainer

    public interface BaseContainer<T>
extends java.lang.Comparable<BaseContainer<T>>, UnknownContainer<T>
    Containers is a value holder, Containers make easy to modify values that needs be final, example: 
     
 int x = 0;
 Consumer<Integer> consumer = (i) -> {
     x += 1;
 };
    The value X needs to be "Local variable x defined in an enclosing scope must be final or effectively final"
    A way to solve this is using Container, see example using Container 
     
 final Container<Integer> x = Container.of(0);
 Consumer<Integer> consumer = (i) -> {
     x.set(x.get()+1);
 };
    also for int you can use IntContainer 
     
 final IntContainer x = new IntContainer(0);
 Consumer<Integer> consumer = (i) -> {
     x.add();
 };
